Boris Johnson will set out a six-point plan to take on Vladimir Putin as bombs continue to drop on day 11 of the Ukraine invasion. The Prime Minister is taking his stand to the global stage following warnings Moscow will consider the declaration of a no-fly zone as participation in the conflict. A second attempt at evacuating civilians in the besieged city of Mariupol will begin at 12pm after a temporary ceasefire was broken by Russia yesterday. More than 11,000 Kremlin troops have been killed so far, Ukraine’s armed forces claimed today. Meanwhile, SpaceX CEO Elon Musk is set to send Starlink internet terminals after a talk with President Volodymyr Zelensky. Follow Metro.co.uk’s live rolling coverage as it happens.